children.subject: That's also what I'd recommend. Math 110 is mostly Math 54 with lots of proofs. I feel like you'd benefit more from 127.

<md>From what I've seen, going into 127 with just MATH 54 background should be sufficient as long as you're confident in your linear algebra abilities. Otherwise, you may find it useful to look into taking 16B before 127 because 16B does cover a lot of the linear algebra content you need to know for 127. If you don't want to take 16B now, then I would recommend to at least go over some of the notes on the course website to gauge your understanding of topics like SVD. </md>

history.content: OP here; thanks for everyone's input! I'll be sticking with 127.

children.subject:
Adding one more perspective for anyone else who reads this post.

  1. It's your choice. Rethink what your skills are and also ask why you want to take 189 now.
  2. Can you prove things using math and words? Go take 127. Do you like math more than engineering? Take 110.
  3. I took the route of 110 -> 104 -> 127, once I finished 104 with a professor who set the bar at grad school, all classes became the same.

Hint: Ask me why I took 127 :)
